Full Description: Founded by physicians in gastroenterology and emergency medicine, RighBio Metrics addresses a very serious problem in healthcare: How do we accurately measure biofluids to enhance the speed and quality of medical treatment – without incurring substantial costs? RightBio Metrics was founded by Paul Gilbert MD, Board Certified in Emergency Medicine, and his father, Robert Gilbert MD, Board Certified in Gastroenterology in 2005. Dr. Paul Gilbert’s first-hand experience with tube misplacement and the frustration experienced in emergency medicine with uncertainty about treatment-critical metrics lead to a passion for developing more appropriate technologies. The innovations by the Drs. Gilbert, while leveraging widely acclaimed measurement practices, represent a revolution in the technologies that deliver such metrics – to enable better patient care and prevent severe accidents. This fully closed system safeguards both clinicians and patients from exposure to aspirate and is indicated for use in neonates, pediatrics, and adults. Utilizing the RightSpotpH® Indicator ensures accurate and reliable confirmation of NG/OG tube placement, enhancing patient safety and care. The RightSpotpH® Indicator is now available with ENFit Connectors so adapters are no longer necessary.  *ENFit is a registered trademark of GEDSA.
